  "body": "On a Polygon mainnet fork using Infura, when I impersonate an account and connect to a contract with the impersonated address and interact with the contract, the hardhat node log shows that the contract interaction is from a random address each time I am interacting with the contract rather than the impersonated address. \r\nNote: I am using hardhat-deploy.\r\n\r\nBelow is a code which illustrates how I am impersonating the account and interacting with the contracts:\r\n\r\n```\r\n// get the contract instance\r\nconst contract = await ethers.getContract(\"Contract\");\r\nconst impersonatedAddress = \"0x84D34f4f83a87596Cd3FB6887cFf8F17Bf5A7B83\";\r\n\r\n// impersonate account \r\nawait hre.network.provider.request({\r\n    method: \"hardhat_impersonateAccount\",\r\n    params: [impersonatedAddress],\r\n  });\r\nconst signer = await ethers.getSigner(impersonatedAddress);\r\n\r\n// contract calling .callA function using the impersonated signer \r\nawait contract.connect(signer).callA();\r\n\r\n// contract calling .callB function using the impersonated signer \r\nawait contract.connect(signer).callB();\r\n```",
